HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 31
BY REPRESENTATIVE WALTERS
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Chief Judge Ree Casey Jones and Caddo Juvenile Court
on the achievements of S.T.A.R. Court, Louisiana's first specialized court against
human trafficking
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Chief Judge Ree Casey Jones and Caddo Juvenile Court on the achievements
3 of S.T.A.R. Court, Louisiana's first specialized court against human trafficking.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Chief Judge Ree Casey Jones, the Caddo
5 Juvenile Court, and the Juvenile Probation Department for their efforts to combat human
6 trafficking in the parish; and
7 WHEREAS, Chief Judge Jones, the Caddo Parish Juvenile Court, and the Juvenile
8 Probation Department have worked with the parish's community partners to develop
9 innovative interventions for youth who are at high risk for human trafficking and victims of
10 human trafficking; and
11 WHEREAS, these efforts began in 2013 with the development of the Caddo-Bossier
12 Community Response Team; the multi-disciplinary team calls on community partners to
13 meet every two weeks to develop trauma-informed and comprehensive service plans for
14 high-risk youth and victims of human trafficking; and
15 WHEREAS, the Caddo-Bossier Community Response Team's approach has been
16 replicated in parishes across Louisiana; in 2015, the Specialized Intensive Probation Unit
17 was implemented with two highly-trained and skilled probation officers who supervise a
18 caseload of high-risk and confirmed victims who are involved in the juvenile justice system;
19 and
