1 WHEREAS, S.T.A.R. Court was introduced in Caddo Parish on March 1, 2019; the
2 court is Louisiana's first trafficking-specific specialized court; the court uses a phase system
3 and incentives to encourage participants to follow the conditions of probation, make better
4 choices, and participate in long-term treatment, support, and recovery; and
5 WHEREAS, S.T.A.R. Court's specialized response system is most deserving of the
6 highest recognition for providing unique opportunities, treatment, and support for Caddo
7 Parish youth and the community at large.
8 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
9 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Chief Judge Ree Casey Jones and Caddo
10 Juvenile Court on the achievements of Louisiana's first S.T.A.R. Court against human
11 trafficking and does hereby extend enduring appreciation for their efforts to support and
12 protect Caddo Parish at-risk youth.
